definition: lit. to give each one a flogging of fifty strokes (idiom)/fig. to punish the guilty and the innocent alike/to put the blame on both parties
pinyin: ge4 da3 wu3 shi2 da4 ban3

definition: the one who has retreated 50 steps laughs at the one who has retreated 100 steps (idiom)/the pot calls the kettle black
pinyin: wu3 shi2 bu4 xiao4 bai3 bu4

sentences.english: Existing staff of 50 people, the plant located in the east village Humen.
sentences.chinese: 现有员工五十余人，总厂设在虎门东风村。

sentences.english: The hotel charged 150 dollors a day,the meal is not included.
sentences.chinese: 这家旅馆一天收费一百五十美元，不包括膳食。

sentences.english: In nineteen eighty, the American divorce rate was about fifty percent.
sentences.chinese: 在一九八四，美国的离婚率是百分之五十左右。

sentences.english: In our class there are fifty students , most of whom are good at English .
sentences.chinese: 我们班有五十个学生，大多数英语都学得很好。

sentences.english: They will charge you fifty dollars for a half-hour, and you won't be able to windsurf.
sentences.chinese: 他们半小时收费五十元，你根柢冲不起来。

sentences.english: The prisoner had on his feet fetters weighing fifty pounds.
sentences.chinese: 这犯人的脚上有一对五十斤重的铁球。

sentences.english: It comes to about eleven and a half million dollars.
sentences.chinese: 这样大概是一千一百五十万美元。

sentences.english: They sent therefore fifty men； and they sought three days， but found him not.
sentences.chinese: 他们便打发五十人去，寻梢了三天，也没有找着。

sentences.english: It is only about a fifty minutes ride.
sentences.chinese: 驱车只有五十分钟的路程。

sentences.english: When the program began artists received eight hundred fifty dollars.
sentences.chinese: 当程序开始的艺术家收到八百五十美元。

sentences.english: Ok, there is an available one, one day 50 yuan please.
sentences.chinese: 好的，这有一部空车，一天五十元。

sentences.english: I spent fifty yuan on a new dictionary.
sentences.chinese: 我花了五十元钱买了一本新词典。

sentences.english: In our class there are fifty-one students.
sentences.chinese: 我们班有五十一名学生。

sentences.english: Something happened in the late 1950s and early ’60s.
sentences.chinese: 五十年代末六十年代初有不少这种事。

sentences.english: Programming has been essentially a solitary profession for the last five decades.
sentences.chinese: 在过去五十年里，编程基本上是一种单干的职业。

sentences.english: Fifty human years are equal to one day & night among the Devas of the Four Great Kings.
sentences.chinese: 人间五十年，是四大王天天神的一昼夜。

definition: more than ten/a dozen or more
